**Creating a Form Input Field for Unique Identifiers**

When creating a form input field for collecting unique identifiers like driver's license numbers or passport numbers, it's essential to consider security and user experience. Here's an example of how to create such a field using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript:

### HTML

```html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Unique Identifier Input Field</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <form id="unique-identifier-form">
        <label for="unique-identifier">Unique Identifier:</label>
        <input type="text" id="unique-identifier" name="unique-identifier" placeholder="Enter your driver's license number or passport number">
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
    </form>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

